{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnectionref\/close(cancellable:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionRef\/IOStreamProtocol-Implementations"]]},"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GIO","symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"title":"close(cancellable:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:3GIO16IOStreamProtocolPAAE5close11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO16TLSConnectionRefV"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionRef\/close(cancellable:)"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it. This will also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"close the individual input and output streams, if they are not already","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"closed."}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once the stream is closed, all other operations will return","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closed"},{"type":"text","text":". Closing a stream multiple times will not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return an error."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Closing a stream will automatically flush any outstanding buffers"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the stream.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Streams will be automatically closed when the last reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is dropped, but you might want to call this function to make sure"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"resources are released as early as possible."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some streams might keep the backing store of the stream (e.g. a file"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"descriptor) open after the stream is closed. See the documentation for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the individual stream for details.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On failure the first error that happened will be reported, but the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"close operation will finish as much as possible. A stream that failed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to close will still return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closed"},{"text":" for all operations.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Still, it is important to check and report the error to the user,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"otherwise there might be a loss of data as all data might not be written."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not NULL, then the operation can be cancelled by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"was cancelled, the error ","type":"text"},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be returned.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Cancelling a close will still leave the stream closed, but some streams"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can use a faster close that doesn’t block to e.g. check errors."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default implementation of this method just calls close on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"individual input\/output streams."}]}]}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSConnectionRef/close(cancellable:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionRef\/close(cancellable:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it. This will also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"close the individual input and output streams, if they are not already","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"closed."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnectionref\/close(cancellable:)","kind":"symbol","title":"close(cancellable:)","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/IOStream":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/iostream","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream","title":"IOStream","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"IOStream","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOStream"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOStream"},{"type":"text","text":" represents an object that has both read and write streams."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Generally the two streams act as separate input and output streams,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but they share some common resources and state. For instance, for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"seekable streams, both streams may use the same position."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSConnectionRef":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnectionref","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TLSConnectionRef"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTlsConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" is the base TLS connection class type, which wraps"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a [class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream"},{"type":"text","text":"] and provides TLS encryption on top of it. Its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"subclasses, [iface","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSClientConnection","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[iface","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSServerConnection","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"], implement client-side and server-side TLS,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"respectively."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionRef","title":"TLSConnectionRef","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TLSConnectionRef","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSServerConnection":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSServerConnection","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TLSServerConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"TLSServerConnection","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsserverconnection","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TLSServerConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GTlsServerConnection","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is the server-side subclass of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnection"},{"text":"], representing a server-side TLS connection.","type":"text"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSClientConnection":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsclientconnection","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSClientConnection","title":"TLSClientConnection","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TLSClientConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TLSClientConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTlsClientConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" is the client-side subclass of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[class","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnection"},{"text":"], representing a client-side TLS connection.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSConnectionRef/IOStreamProtocol-Implementations":{"abstract":[],"role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionRef\/IOStreamProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","title":"IOStreamProtocol Implementations","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnectionref\/iostreamprotocol-implementations"}}}